Package com.rb.nonbiz.math.stats

Class StatisticalSummaryOfStatisticalSummariesCalculator.StatisticalSummaryOfStatisticalSummaries

java.lang.Object
com.rb.nonbiz.math.stats.StatisticalSummaryOfStatisticalSummariesCalculator.StatisticalSummaryOfStatisticalSummaries
Enclosing class:
StatisticalSummaryOfStatisticalSummariesCalculator
public static class StatisticalSummaryOfStatisticalSummariesCalculator.StatisticalSummaryOfStatisticalSummaries
extends java.lang.Object
This is useful if we have a collection of StatisticalSummary (e.g. one per day in a backtest) and we want to store a StatisticalSummary for each of the attributes of a StatisticalSummary. That is, this allows us to store the min of the averages (over the collection), the max of the mins, etc. It is a static inner class so that we can prevent its instantiation from any other place, which saves this data class from having to worry about having preconditions, of which we'd need many if we were able to build this object arbitrarily by setting each of its constituents separately.
